ass=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/Basic.html#intervalIntegral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**First mean value theorem for interval integrals (arbitrary measure, a.e. nonnegativity).**\nLet `f g : ℝ → ℝ` and let `μ` be a measure on `ℝ`. Assume that `f` is continuous on `uIcc a b`,\nthat `g` is interval integrable on `a..b` w.r.t. `μ`, and that `g ≥ 0` a.e. on `Ι a b` w.r.t.\n`μ.restrict (Ι a b)`. Then\n`∃ c ∈ uIcc a b, (∫ x in a..b, f x * g x ∂μ) = f c * (∫ x in a..b, g x ∂μ)`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/MeanValue.html#exists_eq_const_mul_intervalIntegral_of_ae_nonneg","kind":"theorem","line":42,"name":"exists_eq_const_mul_intervalIntegral_of_ae_nonneg","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/MeanValue.lean#L42-L70"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.IntervalIntegral.Basic","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.MeanValue"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.IntervalIntegral.MeanValue"}